text: The following lists events that happened in 1965 in Iceland. ==Incumbents== *President - Ásgeir Ásgeirsson *Prime Minister - Bjarni Benediktsson ==Events== ==Births== Björk *27 February - Bjarkey Gunnarsdóttir, politician. *20 March - Vigdís Hauksdóttir, politician. *17 April - Andrés Guðmundsson, strongman *14 July - Þórdís Gísladóttir, children's writer, poet, novelist and textbook writer *21 July - Guðni Bergsson, footballer *24 July - Disa Eythorsdottir, bridge player *1 November - Björk, singer-songwriter ==Deaths== ==References== Category:1960s in Iceland Iceland Iceland Category:Years of the 20th century in Iceland
title: 1965 in Iceland
